.TH "snd_soc_new_ac97_component" 9 "snd_soc_new_ac97_component" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_soc_new_ac97_component \- initailise AC97 device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct snd_ac97 *" snd_soc_new_ac97_component
.BI "(struct snd_soc_component *component "  ","
.BI "unsigned int id "  ","
.BI "unsigned int id_mask "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "component" 12
audio component
.IP "id" 12
The expected device ID
.IP "id_mask" 12
Mask that is applied to the device ID before comparing with \fIid\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Initialises AC97 component resources for use by ad-hoc devices only.

If \fIid\fP is not 0 this function will reset the device, then read the ID from
the device and check if it matches the expected ID. If it doesn't match an
error will be returned and device will not be registered.
.SH "RETURN"
A \fBPTR_ERR\fP on failure or a valid snd_ac97 struct on success.
